                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a pawnbroker; this sheet was pawned the 3d of April, about six in the evening, by the prisoner.</p>
               <p>(The sheet marked I. E. deposed to by Mr. Evans.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17890422-65-person601">
                  JOHN
                   PENLEY
               <interp inst="t17890422-65-person601" type="surname" value="PENLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890422-65-person601" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890422-65-person601" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>The prisoner came to my shop on the 3d of April to sell a bolster and sheet; he said they were his own, he asked me 5 s. for them; he then said, he had a bed and bedding at home at his lodgings in James's-street; I went home with him, and looked at them; he asked me 1 l. 2 s. I bid him 15 s. I did not then pay for them, but went to a Justice, and gave information; and we went and took the prisoner, sitting on the bed, in Oxford-street.</p>
               <p>(The sheet and bolster deposed to by Mrs. Evans.)</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178904220059"></xptr>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was brought into this scrape by a young woman who took the lodgings of another young man.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17890422-65-verdict295" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17890422-65-verdict295" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
